Critical findings from the code:

campaigns.status = 'complete' is written at line 2306–2310, before analysis/scoring/report runs. A campaign can be complete in the DB with no scores and no report.
There is no persistent record of whether analysis or report generation succeeded — only sys.exit(1) if it fails, leaving the DB in an internally inconsistent state.
The comment at line 2319–2322 already acknowledges this tension but the state model hasn't caught up.
Run context quality is captured to JSON sidecar files per cycle, never aggregated or stored in the DB in any queryable form.
